00:35:37.300 --> 00:35:38.300
Peace.

00:35:38.300 --> 00:35:42.790
&gt;&gt;Male #2: I suppose some of us, myself included,
feel like we did leave a blueprint.

00:35:42.790 --> 00:35:49.090
If you had experienced the euphoria that we
felt during the 60's,when we would see one

00:35:49.090 --> 00:35:53.480
another on a corner, and there wasn't no such
thing as you had to throw up some kinda gang

00:35:53.480 --> 00:35:54.480
sign.

00:35:54.480 --> 00:35:56.950
When you saw the black people, you weren't
like this, they weren't like that.

00:35:56.950 --> 00:35:57.950
Everything was just fine.

00:35:57.950 --> 00:36:00.910
That's not the way it is now.

00:36:00.910 --> 00:36:04.260
I thought, me as an individual 'cause I can't
speak to other people.

00:36:04.260 --> 00:36:08.910
I thought there would be a continuum, I thought
if I raised my children a certain way that

00:36:08.910 --> 00:36:10.660
things would stay that way.

00:36:10.660 --> 00:36:13.280
I thought that we were progressing.

00:36:13.280 --> 00:36:17.970
I underestimated the seriousness of our enemies.

00:36:17.970 --> 00:36:19.690
I underestimated them.

00:36:19.690 --> 00:36:26.660
That so much time and effort would be spent
in dismantling those things that brought about

00:36:26.660 --> 00:36:29.859
self-esteem, those things that brought about
self-love.

00:36:29.859 --> 00:36:32.430
Those things that brought about respect for
one another.

00:36:32.430 --> 00:36:37.340
A great deal of time and energy was spent
dismantling that.

00:36:37.340 --> 00:36:38.910
By our enemies.

00:36:38.910 --> 00:36:41.210
And it is our fault.

00:36:41.210 --> 00:36:44.570
That we did not see that for what it was.

00:36:44.570 --> 00:36:46.560
And combat it more thoroughly.

00:36:46.560 --> 00:36:52.200
&gt;&gt;Male #3: I think maybe we did leave you
a blueprint.

00:36:52.200 --> 00:37:03.120
And yet, we too were so busy trying to survive,
that we were not as organized and disciplined

00:37:03.120 --> 00:37:05.890
as maybe we should have been.

00:37:05.890 --> 00:37:11.250
But speaking from the platform of Martin Luther
King's civil right's movement.

00:37:11.250 --> 00:37:14.580
Martin Luther King never had more than 100
people on his staff.

00:37:14.580 --> 00:37:18.160
And that was only for one or two movements.

00:37:18.160 --> 00:37:24.520
He never had more than a half a million dollars
a year to try to change the world.

00:37:24.520 --> 00:37:27.010
None of us had a blueprint.

00:37:27.010 --> 00:37:40.170
But what he taught us to do and what we learned
from Gandhi in India, was that we could find

00:37:40.170 --> 00:37:45.020
our own way by standing up for the truth.

00:37:45.020 --> 00:37:53.030
&gt;&gt;Male #4 Well, after the civil rights movement
of the 60's proved to be very very successful,

00:37:53.030 --> 00:37:59.980
I think blacks felt that we have crossed a
threshold, and it's easy going from here on

00:37:59.980 --> 00:38:00.980
in.

00:38:00.980 --> 00:38:04.620
But the worst was yet to come.

00:38:04.620 --> 00:38:10.750
I kinda think we thought that the waves would
continue to roll.

00:38:10.750 --> 00:38:14.750
And we did drop the ball.

00:38:14.750 --> 00:38:20.900
Only to find out later that other people were
making plans and were putting certain kinds

00:38:20.900 --> 00:38:25.090
of Negroes in heads of organizations and paying
them well.

00:38:25.090 --> 00:38:29.160
And they became the spokespersons for black
people.

00:38:29.160 --> 00:38:32.859
And they became the protectors of the plantation.

00:38:32.859 --> 00:38:34.460
Being paid by white people.

00:38:34.460 --> 00:38:39.650
&gt;&gt;Male #5: I think that we left you the blueprint,
we just didn't tell you where it was.

00:38:39.650 --> 00:38:41.090
It's there.

00:38:41.090 --> 00:38:44.400
But we didn't just show it to you or lay it
out.

00:38:44.400 --> 00:38:48.010
You had to look at us and see what we were
doing to find out.

00:38:48.010 --> 00:38:49.780
How to go about that blueprint.

00:38:49.780 --> 00:38:52.150
You see, some things can't be explained to
you.

00:38:52.150 --> 00:38:55.780
Some things you gotta look at a person and
then you gotta see what it is that they're

00:38:55.780 --> 00:38:56.780
doing.

00:38:56.780 --> 00:38:58.970
The blueprint is, you get an education.

00:38:58.970 --> 00:39:00.470
You don't just be in the middle of the road.

00:39:00.470 --> 00:39:02.660
You don't try to be with the kids who don't
do well.

00:39:02.660 --> 00:39:04.770
You try to be the best.

00:39:04.770 --> 00:39:05.770
OK?

00:39:05.770 --> 00:39:10.530
You do as good as you can, no matter how angry
people become when you're really good.

00:39:10.530 --> 00:39:11.530
You know, what?

00:39:11.530 --> 00:39:15.090
Success is not easy.

00:39:15.090 --> 00:39:16.190
It is not.

00:39:16.190 --> 00:39:19.920
If it was, everybody would be successful.

00:39:19.920 --> 00:39:21.930
It takes time.

00:39:21.930 --> 00:39:24.390
It takes hard work.

00:39:24.390 --> 00:39:27.580
And everybody's not geared for hard work.

00:39:27.580 --> 00:39:28.940
Some people want it overnight.

00:39:28.940 --> 00:39:31.250
And it's not gonna happen that way.

00:39:31.250 --> 00:39:36.080
So what you have to do it, we old people,
we've laid the groundwork for you.

00:39:36.080 --> 00:39:37.510
We've already put the blueprint out there.

00:39:37.510 --> 00:39:40.960
Now you might not like that blueprint.

00:39:40.960 --> 00:39:43.290
You might wanna alter it in some way.

00:39:43.290 --> 00:39:45.590
And you can.

00:39:45.590 --> 00:39:50.480
But if you alter it, and it's not for the
better, you will not achieve what us old folks

00:39:50.480 --> 00:39:53.450
have achieved.

00:39:53.450 --> 00:39:58.410
&gt;&gt; Chris: So again, you can imagine.

00:39:58.410 --> 00:40:00.690
You can see that what we're doing is, we're
telling a story.

00:40:00.690 --> 00:40:05.000
We're allowing the men in this project to
tell the story.

00:40:05.000 --> 00:40:09.410
And in this case there was a hunger for an
intergenerational exchange that doesn't happen

00:40:09.410 --> 00:40:13.359
when the men don't have fathers and grandfathers
who are there.

00:40:13.359 --> 00:40:18.800
And so this project becomes a vehicle for
talking between generations.

00:40:18.800 --> 00:40:20.520
